cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on visual tasks and proposes a method for aggregating convolutional features into an SPD matrix representation through an end-to-end deep network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces new layers in the network, indicating a focus on deep learning, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of SPD matrices and their transformation suggests a focus on mathematical foundations, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for learning a robust representation, which is a common theme in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper conducts experiments on visual classification, indicating a focus on multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
